message.content:
Analysis of the Target Structure:

•  Total Block Count and Layers  
  – There are 8 total blocks.  
  – They form three “levels”:  
    1) Bottom layer     → 2 red arch‐shaped blocks side by side  
    2) Middle “belt”  → 4 yellow rectangular blocks forming a band around the center  
    3) Top layer        → 2 red arch‐shaped blocks side by side (aligned above the bottom pair)  

•  Spatial Arrangement  
  – The two red blocks on the bottom stand like an “H” when viewed from the side.  
  – Four yellow planks wrap around horizontally in the middle (front, back, left, right).  
  – Two more red arch blocks sit on top, aligned with the bottom pair, leaving a gap in the center.  

Selection of Dictionary Blocks:

1) Red Arch Blocks  
   – Use block #1 for the “left‐arch” orientation and block #2 for the “right‐arch” orientation.  
   – Two of each are required (2 × #1 and 2 × #2 = 4 red arches).  

2) Yellow Rectangular Blocks  
   – Use block #9 (front), #10 (back), #13 (left), and #14 (right) to match the four mid‐level planks exactly as shown.  

Proposed Assembly Order:

{
  Step1: Move block with index 1    // bottom left arch  
  Step2: Move block with index 2    // bottom right arch  
  Step3: Move block with index 9    // middle front plank  
  Step4: Move block with index 10   // middle back plank  
  Step5: Move block with index 13   // middle left plank  
  Step6: Move block with index 14   // middle right plank  
  Step7: Move block with index 1    // top left arch  
  Step8: Move block with index 2    // top right arch  
}
